#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:5
msgid "Marking test functions with attributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:8
msgid ""
"By using the ``pytest.mark`` helper you can easily set metadata on your test "
"functions. There are some builtin markers, for example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:12
msgid ":ref:`skip <skip>` - always skip a test function"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:13
msgid ""
":ref:`skipif <skipif>` - skip a test function if a certain condition is met"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:14
msgid ""
":ref:`xfail <xfail>` - produce an \"expected failure\" outcome if a certain "
"condition is met"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:16
msgid ""
":ref:`parametrize <parametrizemark>` to perform multiple calls to the same "
"test function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:19
msgid ""
"It's easy to create custom markers or to apply markers to whole test classes "
"or modules. See :ref:`mark examples` for examples which also serve as "
"documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:25
msgid ""
"Marks can only be applied to tests, having no effect on :ref:`fixtures "
"<fixtures>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:30
msgid "Raising errors on unknown marks: --strict"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:32
msgid ""
"When the ``--strict`` command-line flag is passed, any marks not registered "
"in the ``pytest.ini`` file will trigger an error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:34
msgid "Marks can be registered like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:36
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"markers =\n"
"    slow\n"
"    serial"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:43
msgid ""
"This can be used to prevent users mistyping mark names by accident. Test "
"suites that want to enforce this should add ``--strict`` to ``addopts``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:46
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = --strict\n"
"markers =\n"
"    slow\n"
"    serial"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:58
msgid "Marker revamp and iteration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:62
msgid ""
"pytest's marker implementation traditionally worked by simply updating the "
"``__dict__`` attribute of functions to cumulatively add markers. As a "
"result, markers would unintentionally be passed along class hierarchies in "
"surprising ways. Further, the API for retrieving them was inconsistent, as "
"markers from parameterization would be stored differently than markers "
"applied using the ``@pytest.mark`` decorator and markers added via ``node."
"add_marker``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:64
msgid ""
"This state of things made it technically next to impossible to use data from "
"markers correctly without having a deep understanding of the internals, "
"leading to subtle and hard to understand bugs in more advanced usages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:66
msgid ""
"Depending on how a marker got declared/changed one would get either a "
"``MarkerInfo`` which might contain markers from sibling classes, "
"``MarkDecorators`` when marks came from parameterization or from a ``node."
"add_marker`` call, discarding prior marks. Also ``MarkerInfo`` acts like a "
"single mark, when it in fact represents a merged view on multiple marks with "
"the same name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:69
msgid ""
"On top of that markers were not accessible the same way for modules, "
"classes, and functions/methods. In fact, markers were only accessible in "
"functions, even if they were declared on classes/modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:72
msgid ""
"A new API to access markers has been introduced in pytest 3.6 in order to "
"solve the problems with the initial design, providing :func:`_pytest.nodes."
"Node.iter_markers` method to iterate over markers in a consistent manner and "
"reworking the internals, which solved great deal of problems with the "
"initial design."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:78
msgid "Updating code"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:80
msgid ""
"The old ``Node.get_marker(name)`` function is considered deprecated because "
"it returns an internal ``MarkerInfo`` object which contains the merged name, "
"``*args`` and ``**kwargs`` of all the markers which apply to that node."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:83
msgid "In general there are two scenarios on how markers should be handled:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:85
msgid ""
"1. Marks overwrite each other. Order matters but you only want to think of "
"your mark as a single item. E.g. ``log_level('info')`` at a module level can "
"be overwritten by ``log_level('debug')`` for a specific test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:88
msgid "In this case, use ``Node.get_closest_marker(name)``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:90
msgid ""
"# replace this:\n"
"marker = item.get_marker(\"log_level\")\n"
"if marker:\n"
"    level = marker.args[0]\n"
"\n"
"# by this:\n"
"marker = item.get_closest_marker(\"log_level\")\n"
"if marker:\n"
"    level = marker.args[0]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:102
msgid ""
"2. Marks compose in an additive manner. E.g. ``skipif(condition)`` marks "
"mean you just want to evaluate all of them, order doesn't even matter. You "
"probably want to think of your marks as a set here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:105
msgid ""
"In this case iterate over each mark and handle their ``*args`` and "
"``**kwargs`` individually."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:107
msgid ""
"# replace this\n"
"skipif = item.get_marker(\"skipif\")\n"
"if skipif:\n"
"    for condition in skipif.args:\n"
"        # eval condition\n"
"        ...\n"
"\n"
"# by this:\n"
"for skipif in item.iter_markers(\"skipif\"):\n"
"    condition = skipif.args[0]\n"
"    # eval condition"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:122
msgid ""
"If you are unsure or have any questions, please consider opening `an issue "
"<https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:126
msgid "Related issues"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:128
msgid ""
"Here is a non-exhaustive list of issues fixed by the new implementation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:130
msgid ""
"Marks don't pick up nested classes (`#199 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/199>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:132
msgid ""
"Markers stain on all related classes (`#568 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/issues/568>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:134
msgid ""
"Combining marks - args and kwargs calculation (`#2897 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2897>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:136
msgid ""
"``request.node.get_marker('name')`` returns ``None`` for markers applied in "
"classes (`#902 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/902>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:138
msgid ""
"Marks applied in parametrize are stored as markdecorator (`#2400 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2400>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:140
msgid ""
"Fix marker interaction in a backward incompatible way (`#1670 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1670>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:142
msgid ""
"Refactor marks to get rid of the current \"marks transfer\" mechanism "
"(`#2363 <https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2363>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:144
msgid ""
"Introduce FunctionDefinition node, use it in generate_tests (`#2522 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/2522>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:146
msgid ""
"Remove named marker attributes and collect markers in items (`#891 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/891>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:148
msgid ""
"skipif mark from parametrize hides module level skipif mark (`#1540 <https://"
"github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/1540>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:150
msgid ""
"skipif + parametrize not skipping tests (`#1296 <https://github.com/pytest-"
"dev/pytest/issues/1296>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:152
msgid ""
"Marker transfer incompatible with inheritance (`#535 <https://github.com/"
"pytest-dev/pytest/issues/535>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:154
msgid ""
"More details can be found in the `original PR <https://github.com/pytest-dev/"
"pytest/pull/3317>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:158
msgid ""
"in a future major relase of pytest we will introduce class based markers, at "
"which points markers will no longer be limited to instances of :py:class:"
"`Mark`"
msgstr ""
